data structure

§EnglishEdit

§PronunciationEdit

  • Audio (US)
    		(file)

§NounEdit

Examples

matrix, stack, queue, dequeue, list, vector, scene graph

data structure (plural data structures)

  1. (computer science) Any way of storing and organizing data in a computer so that it can be used efficiently.
